<h1>SgbMap</h1>
<p>The main map component. Renders an interactive MapLibre GL JS map with configurable styles, structured child sections, controls, sources, overlays, and popups.</p>

<h2 id="canonical_structure">// canonical_structure</h2>
<p>Use three child content sections for component markup. Put controls in <code>MapControls</code>, MapLibre data sources in <code>MapSources</code>, and app overlays in <code>MapOverlays</code>. Sections make ownership clear and produce placement errors when components are nested in the wrong place.</p>
<CodeBlock Language="razor" Files="@_canonicalStructure" />

<h2 id="basic_usage">// basic_usage</h2>
<p>Provide a center coordinate and zoom level. The default style is OpenFreeMap Liberty, a clean vector style that requires no API key. Add controls inside <code>MapControls</code> with subcomponents such as <code>MapNavigationControl</code>, <code>MapScaleControl</code>, and <code>MapLegendControl</code>. <code>FitBoundsOptions</code> auto-fits the viewport to a set of feature IDs.</p>
<ExampleView TComponent="BasicMapExample">
    <BasicMapExample />
</ExampleView>

<h2 id="fit_bounds_padding">// fit_bounds_padding</h2>
<p><code>FitBoundsOptions</code> fits the map viewport to a set of features. Use <code>Padding</code> for uniform spacing on all sides, or <code>TopLeftPadding</code> and <code>BottomRightPadding</code> for asymmetric padding when UI elements like sidebars overlap the map. The <code>CenterMapControl</code> button automatically reads the current <code>MapOptions</code> to re-center.</p>
<ExampleView TComponent="FitBoundsPaddingExample">
    <FitBoundsPaddingExample />
</ExampleView>

<h2 id="custom_controls">// custom_controls</h2>
<p>Use control subcomponents inside <code>MapControls</code> for built-in controls, styled custom controls, and legends. Available built-ins are <code>MapNavigationControl</code>, <code>MapScaleControl</code>, <code>MapFullscreenControl</code>, <code>MapGeolocateControl</code>, <code>MapTerrainControl</code>, and <code>MapCenterControl</code>.</p>
<p>Use first-class styled controls for common custom UI. <code>MapActionControl</code> renders one action button with library chrome. <code>MapToggleControl</code> renders one stateful button with <code>aria-pressed</code> and <code>PressedChanged</code>. <code>MapControlButtonGroup</code> hosts related <code>MapControlButton</code> and <code>MapControlToggleButton</code> children with the same chrome.</p>
<table>
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>Need</th>
            <th>Use</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td>Single command button</td>
            <td><code>MapActionControl</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Single pressed or unpressed state</td>
            <td><code>MapToggleControl</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Related action and toggle buttons</td>
            <td><code>MapControlButtonGroup</code> with button children</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Legend and layer visibility</td>
            <td><code>MapLegendControl</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Panel or status content</td>
            <td>Future <code>MapPanelControl</code> or <code>MapStatusControl</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Fully custom markup</td>
            <td><code>MapCustomControl</code> escape hatch</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>
<CodeBlock Language="razor" Files="@_customControlExamples" />
<p>Use <code>MapCustomControl</code> only when the UI needs custom markup that the styled primitives do not cover. Blazor still renders the content and handles events such as <code>@@onclick</code> and <code>@@bind</code>. JavaScript creates the MapLibre control shell, places it, orders it, and removes it.</p>
<p>Use <code>MapLegendControl</code> for component-first legends with collapsible chrome, item templates, visibility groups, and visibility callbacks. Component controls are explicit: maps render no controls by default. The record-backed <code>Controls</code> API remains available for advanced composition, but component markup is the preferred authoring model.</p>
<p>Ordering is deterministic per map corner: controls are sorted by <code>Order</code> ascending, then declaration order, then <code>ControlId</code> as a stable tie-breaker. Keep each control <code>Id</code> unique.</p>
<ExampleView TComponent="CustomControlsExample">
    <CustomControlsExample />
</ExampleView>

<h2 id="styles">// styles</h2>
<p>Swap between built-in style presets using the <code>MapOptions.Style</code> property. The library ships with <code>MapStyle.OpenFreeMap.Liberty</code>, <code>Positron</code>, and <code>Bright</code>. Use <code>MapStyle.FromUrl</code> or <code>MapStyle.FromRasterUrl</code> for custom sources. Because <code>MapOptions</code> is a record, change styles reactively with a <code>with</code> expression.</p>
<ExampleView TComponent="StyleSwitchingExample">
    <StyleSwitchingExample />
</ExampleView>

<h2 id="themes">// themes</h2>
<p>The <code>Theme</code> parameter controls UI chrome appearance (controls, popups, attribution). It has no effect on tile rendering. Pass <code>MapTheme.Dark</code> to switch to dark chrome. Hover the marker below and toggle themes to see the popup styling change.</p>
<ExampleView TComponent="ThemeSwitchingExample">
    <ThemeSwitchingExample />
</ExampleView>

<h2 id="markers">// markers</h2>
<p>DOM-based markers with optional drag, custom colors, and icons. Pass a list of <code>Marker</code> records to the <code>Markers</code> parameter. Key options include <code>Title</code>, <code>Color</code>, <code>Draggable</code>, <code>Scale</code>, and <code>Icon</code>.</p>
<ExampleView TComponent="MarkersExample">
    <MarkersExample />
</ExampleView>

<h2 id="circles_and_polylines">// circles_and_polylines</h2>
<p>GPU-rendered shapes for higher performance. <code>Circle</code> and <code>Polyline</code> records are rendered via MapLibre GL's WebGL pipeline. They render efficiently at large counts and support data-driven styling.</p>
<ExampleView TComponent="CirclesAndPolylinesExample">
    <CirclesAndPolylinesExample />
</ExampleView>

<h2 id="entity_and_list_overlays">// entity_and_list_overlays</h2>
<p>Use <code>TrackedEntityLayer</code> for moving, interactive entities that need stable IDs, feature-state driven hover or selection, popups, decorations, clustering, and diffed updates. Use <code>GeoJsonSource</code> for static or externally supplied GeoJSON where you want to define MapLibre layers directly.</p>
<p>Use batch overlay components for app lists such as stations and tracks. They live in <code>MapOverlays</code> and adapt your items with selectors.</p>
<CodeBlock Language="razor" Files="@_overlaySections" />

<h2 id="popups">// popups</h2>
<p>Three trigger modes: click, hover, and permanent. Attach a <code>PopupOptions</code> record to any <code>Marker</code> or <code>Circle</code> via its <code>Popup</code> property. Set <code>CloseButton: false</code> on permanent popups for a cleaner look.</p>
<p><strong>Popup safety:</strong> use <code>PopupOptions.FromText</code> by default. Use <code>PopupOptions.FromRawHtml</code> only with trusted or sanitized HTML.</p>
<ExampleView TComponent="PopupsExample">
    <PopupsExample />
</ExampleView>

<h2 id="wms_raster_styles">// wms_raster_styles</h2>
<p>Use <code>MapStyle.FromWmsUrl</code> to render WMS raster tiles as the base map style. Other factory methods include <code>FromWmtsUrl</code>, <code>FromArcGisMapServer</code>, and <code>FromRasterUrl</code>. To layer raster sources on top of a vector base, use <code>TileOverlay</code> instead.</p>
<ExampleView TComponent="WmsRasterStyleExample">
    <WmsRasterStyleExample />
</ExampleView>

@code {
    private static readonly Dictionary<string, string> _canonicalStructure = new()
    {
        ["SgbMapSections.razor"] = """
            <SgbMap MapOptions="@_mapOptions" ContainerClass="rail-map">
                <MapControls>
                    <MapNavigationControl Id="navigation" />
                    <MapLegendControl Id="legend" Definition="@_legend" />
                </MapControls>

                <MapSources>
                    <GeoJsonSource Id="railway" Data="@_railwayGeoJson">
                        <LineLayer Id="tracks" Color="#475569" Width="2" />
                    </GeoJsonSource>
                </MapSources>

                <MapOverlays>
                    <TrackedEntityLayer TItem="Train" Layer="@_trainLayer" />
                    <MapMarkers TItem="Station"
                                Items="@_stations"
                                IdSelector="station => station.Id"
                                PositionSelector="station => station.Position"
                                TitleSelector="station => station.Name" />
                </MapOverlays>
            </SgbMap>
            """,
    };

    private static readonly Dictionary<string, string> _overlaySections = new()
    {
        ["MapOverlays.razor"] = """
            <MapOverlays>
                <TrackedEntityLayer TItem="Train" Layer="@_trainLayer" />

                <MapMarkers TItem="Station"
                            Items="@_stations"
                            IdSelector="station => station.Id"
                            PositionSelector="station => station.Position"
                            TitleSelector="station => station.Name" />

                <MapPolylines TItem="Track"
                              Items="@_tracks"
                              IdSelector="track => track.Id"
                              CoordinatesSelector="track => track.Coordinates"
                              ColorSelector="track => track.Color"
                              WidthSelector="track => 2.0" />
            </MapOverlays>
            """,
    };

    private static readonly Dictionary<string, string> _customControlExamples = new()
    {
        ["MapActionControl.razor"] = """
            <MapActionControl Id="focus-station"
                              Position="ControlPosition.TopLeft"
                              Label="Focus station"
                              Text="Central Station"
                              OnClick="FocusStationAsync" />
            """,
        ["MapToggleControl.razor"] = """
            <MapToggleControl Id="station-labels"
                              Position="ControlPosition.TopLeft"
                              Label="Toggle station labels"
                              Text="Labels"
                              Pressed="@_labelsVisible"
                              PressedChanged="value => _labelsVisible = value" />
            """,
        ["MapControlButtonGroup.razor"] = """
            <MapControlButtonGroup Id="map-tools" Label="Map tools">
                <MapControlButton Label="Zoom to network" Text="Network" OnClick="ZoomToNetworkAsync" />
                <MapControlToggleButton Label="Show alerts"
                                        Text="Alerts"
                                        Pressed="@_alertsVisible"
                                        PressedChanged="value => _alertsVisible = value" />
            </MapControlButtonGroup>
            """,
    };
}
